TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hollifield, Burton
AU  - Miller, Robert A.
AU  - Sandås, Patrik
T1  - Empirical Analysis of Limit Order Markets
PY  - 2004
Y1  - 2004/10/01
DO  - 10.1111/0034-6527.00313
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 71
IS  - 4
SP  - 1027
EP  - 1063
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We provide empirical restrictions of a model of optimal order submissions in a limit order market. A trader's optimal order submission depends on the trader's valuation for the asset and the trade-offs between order prices, execution probabilities and picking off risks. The optimal order submission strategy is a monotone function of a trader's valuation for the asset. We test the monotonicity restriction in a sample of order submissions and their realized outcomes from the Stockholm Stock Exchange. We do not reject the monotonicity restriction for buy orders or sell orders considered separately, but reject the monotonicity restriction for buy and sell orders considered jointly.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/0034-6527.00313
ER  - 



